# Import paths (core-be)

## Allowed

| Tree | Prefix | Example |
| ---- | ------ | ------- |
| Application code | `@/` | `@/domains/auth/auth.service.js` |
| Tooling scripts | `@tooling/` | `@tooling/setup/common/logger.js` |
| Same folder only | `./` | `./auth.repository.js` (co-located layers) |

- Always use the **`.js` extension** in import specifiers (NodeNext).
- Cross-domain imports in `src/` use `@/domains/<domain>/...` — never `../` to reach another folder.

## Forbidden

- **Parent-relative imports** (`from '../'`, `from '../../'`, …) anywhere under `src/**/*.ts` or `tooling/**/*.ts`.
- Cross-folder relative paths — resolve to `@/` or `@tooling/` instead.

## Enforcement

- CI global test: [`src/tests/global/import-paths.global.test.ts`](../../src/tests/global/import-paths.global.test.ts) (`pnpm test:global`).
- IDE default: `.vscode/settings.json` → `typescript.preferences.importModuleSpecifier: "non-relative"`.
- Path aliases: [`tsconfig.json`](../../tsconfig.json) — `@/*` → `src/*`, `@tooling/*` → `tooling/*`.

## Exemptions

- `src/tests/load/k6/**/*.js` — JavaScript load scripts (not TypeScript).
- Framework-mandated dynamic imports where aliases are impossible (rare; document in PR if added).

